fields.descriptive_line: Selection of accessories belonging to Betty Pinney's dolls' house, 'Bettiscombe'.
fields.physical_description: Selection of accessories belonging to the 'Bettiscombe' dolls' house. Items range from furniture and food, to plants and ornaments.
fields.title: Bettiscombe; Miss Pinney's House
fields.production_note: Attribution note: The house was probably made by an estate carpenter in about 1870 and furnished later by the donor's mother Mrs Betty Pinney. Mrs Pinney made some of the furnishings but many were bought or commissioned.
